\prob{1}

We showed in lecture that
\[
\pi z \cot(\pi z) = 1 + \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{z^2}{z^2-n^2} = 1 -
\sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{z^2}{n^2}\frac{1}{1-z^2/n^2}.
\]
Then for $|z| < 1$ we have
\[
\frac{1}{1-z^2/n^2} = \sum_{k=0}^\infty \frac{z^{2k}}{n^{2k}} \implies
\pi z \cot(\pi z) = 1 - \sum_{n=1}^\infty \sum_{k=1}^\infty
\frac{z^{2k}}{n^{2k}} = \sum_{k=1}^\infty z^{2k} \sum_{n=1}^\infty
n^{-2k}.
\]
By uniqueness of Laurent series it follows that for $k \in \N$,
\[
\sum_{n=1}^\infty n^{-2k} = \frac{1}{(2k)!}
\left.\frac{d^{2k}}{dz^{2k}} \right|_{z=0} \pi z \cot(\pi z)
\]

